Reinsdyret Rudolf?

Bildet er et av mange stemnings- og naturbilder i arkivet etter Landslaget for reiselivet i Norge. Landslaget for Reiselivet i Norge ble stiftet 1903. Det var et offentlig opprettet organ for å fremme reisetrafikken i Norge. Landslaget drev reiselivsreklame i utlandet og i Norge, og utga en rekke brosjyrer og publikasjoner. De hadde et stort bildearkiv som ble brukt i promoteringen av Norge som ferieland.

Fotograf: Normann

Arkivreferanse: Pa_0722_uaa9_9_002

Rudolph the red nosed reindeer?

The photo is one of several photos showing scenery and atmosphere in the archive of Landslaget for reiselivet i Norge (the Norwegian Tourism Association).
The Norwegian Tourism Association was founded in 1903. It was a public body created to promote travelling in Norway. The association advertised abroad and in Norway, and published a series of brochures and publications. They had a large photo archive that was used in the promotion of Norway as a holiday destination.

Photo: Normann
